","\[Epsilon]lgMatUpper","\[CurlyEpsilon]Lower","\[Epsilon]Mat","\[Epsilon]MatLower","\[Epsilon]MatUpper","\[CurlyEpsilon]Upper","\[Zeta]","\[Zeta]Lower","\[Zeta]m","\[Zeta]p","\[Zeta]Upper","\[Eta]","\[Eta]Mat","\[Theta]","\[CapitalTheta]","\[CapitalNu]","\[Sigma]","\[CapitalSigma]","\[Sigma]barVecLower","\[Sigma]barVecUpper","\[Sigma]mat","\[Sigma]matRule","\[Sigma]VecLower","\[Sigma]VecUpper","\[Phi]","\[CapitalOmega]","$SMaSHShortcuts","$SMaSHFunctions","$Helicity","$Kinematics","$Mandelstams"};


(* ::Section:: *)
(*Usage*)


(* ::Input::Initialization:: *)
AddAssumptions::usage="AddAssumptions[List] : Adds the list of assumptions to $Assumptions.";
AllIndepedentMandelstam::usage="AllIndepedentMandelstam[] : Gives the list of all independent Mandelstam variables.";
AllLegs::usage="AllLegs[] : Gives the list of all independent the declared legs.";
AllMandelstam::usage="AllMandelstam[] : Gives the list of all Mandelstam variables.";
AllMassiveLegs::usage="AllMassiveLegs[] : Gives the list of all declared massive legs.";
AllMassiveMomenta::usage="AllMassiveMomenta[] : Gives the list of all declared massive momenta.";
AllMassivePolarizations::usage="AllMassivePolarizations[] : Gives the list of all declared massive polarizations.";
AllMasslessFieldStrengths::usage="AllMasslessFieldStrengths[] : Gives the list of all massless field strengths.";
AllMasslessHelicities::usage="AllMasslessHelicities[] : Gives the list of all massless helicities.";
AllMasslessLegs::usage="AllMasslessLegs[] : Gives the list of all massless legs.";
AllMasslessMomenta::usage="AllMasslessMomenta[] : Gives the list of all massless momenta.";
AllMasslessPolarizations::usage="AllMasslessPolarizations[] : Gives the list of all massless polarizations.";
AllMasslessReferenceSpinors::usage="AllMasslessReferenceSpinors[] : Gives the list of all massless reference spinors.";
AllMomenta::usage="AllMomenta[] : Gives the list of all momenta, massless and massive.";
B::usage="Prefix for the massless field strengths.";
BaseHead::usage="BaseHead[var_] : Gives the base head of the variable i.e., for a variable X[][]...[] it gives X.";
BasisForm::usage="BasisForm[OptionsPattern[]] : Writes the expression in the basis form where the basis is determined using FindBasis. The default options include {pattern -> SHAA[a_, b_] | SHBB[a_, b_] | SHAB[a_, b_, c_], function -> (#1 &)}.";
CanonicalizeIndices::usage="Canonicalizes the contracted little group and spinor indices in an expression.";
CanonicalizeScalars::usage="Canonicalizes the spinor helicity scalars in an expression.";
CanonicalizeSU2LRScalars::usage="Canonicalizes the left- and right-handed spinor helicity scalars in an expression.";
CanonicalizeSU2LScalars::usage="Canonicalizes the left-handed spinor helicity scalars in an expression.";
CanonicalizeSU2RScalars::usage="Canonicalizes the right-handed spinor helicity scalars in an expression.";
CanonicalizeTerms::usage="Canonicalizes the left- and right-handed scalars and applies SimplifySchouten.";
CartesianCoordinates::usage="Converts spherical coordinates to Cartesian coordinates.";
ChargeConjugate::usage="Applies a charge conjugation transformation.";
CheckOnShell::usage="CheckOnShell[label] : Checks the on-shell conditions of the numerics obtained against the label.";
ClearAssumptions::usage="ClearAssumptions[]: Clears all assumptions, any declared data, and the generated numerics.";
ClearMomentumConservation::usage="ClearMomentumConservation[] : Clears the declared momentum conservation. Also clears the Mandelstam rules.";
ClearNumerics::usage="ClearNumerics[label] : Clears the numerical kinematics for the label. The default value of label is the list NumericLabels.";
COM::usage="COM : Option for GenerateNumerics. Default value is False.";
ComplexConjugate::usage="Applies complex conjugation over a SH expression.";
ComplexifyNumerics::usage="Complexifies all massless numerics.";
ComponentForm::usage="Writes the SH expression in terms of momentum components in Cartesian coordinates.";
ComponentNumerics::usage="ComponentNumerics[label] : Stores the momentum component numerical values generated against the label. Options: $Kinematics -> False.";
ComptonCOMFrame::usage="Writes the center of mass expression for Compton scattering. Particles 1 and 2 are massive, whereas 3 and 4 are massless.";
COMrules::usage="Gives the center of mass rules for Compton scattering.";
ContractLorMetric::usage="Contracts the Lorentz spacetime metric.";
ContractMetric::usage="Contracts all possible metrics.";
ContractSU2LGMetric::usage="Contracts the little group antisymmetric bilinear.";
ContractSU2LMetric::usage="Contracts the left-handed antisymmetric bilinear.";
ContractSU2RMetric::usage="Contracts the right-handed antisymmetric bilinear.";
ConvertLortoSH::usage="Converts a Lorentz vector expression to spinor helicity.";
ConvertMettoSH::usage="Converts the Lorentz metric to spinor helicity.";
ConvertMlFStoSH::usage="Converts massless field strengths to spinor helicity.";
ConvertMlPoltoSH::usage="Converts massless polarizations to spinor helicity.";
ConvertMomtoSH::usage="Converts Lorentz momentum to spinor helicity.";
ConvertMsPoltoSH::usage="Converts massive polarizations to spinor helicity.";
Coupling::usage="Coupling[g, i] : Represents the i-th coupling with head g.";
CPT::usage="Applies CPT transformations.";
DeclareMasslessLegs::usage="DeclareMasslessLegs[MlLegs_List] : Declares the MlLegs as massless. The argument can take a list of numbers or symbols.";
DeclareMassiveLegs::usage="DeclareMassiveLegs[MsLegs_List] : Declares the MsLegs as massive. The argument can take a list of numbers or symbols.";
DeclareLegs::usage="DeclareLegs[MsLegs_List][MlLegs_List] : Declares the MlLegs as massless and MsLegs as massive. The argument can take a list of numbers or symbols.";
DeclareMomentumConservation::usage="DeclareMomentumConservation[MomentumConservationEquation] : Defines the Mandelstam variables for the given momentum conservation equation. Options: $Mandelstams -> Automatic";
DecomposetoSU2Basis::usage="DecomposetoSU2Basis[leg] : Decomposes the SH variables for a leg in the SU(2) basis.";
Decompose\[Lambda]to\[Chi]::usage="Decomposes the SU(2) basis elements \[Lambda] to dimensionless spinors \[Chi].";
Dirac\[CapitalPsi]::usage="Dirac\[CapitalPsi][leg, \[Alpha]] : Gives the four-component Dirac spinor.";
DressMom::usage="DressMom[Momenta, \[Alpha], \[Beta]] : Places the spinor indices \[Alpha], \[Beta] over the linear combination Momenta.";
DressSH::usage="Same as DressMom.";
EditMassiveData::usage="EditMassiveData[] : Opens the palette for massive legs, which can then be edited.";
EditMasslessData::usage="EditMasslessData[] : Opens the palette for massless legs, which can then be edited.";
epsilon\[Eta]::usage="4D Levi-Civita tensor.";
FGProjector::usage="FGProjector[S, k, m, LeftPrefix, RightPrefix, LeftSymm, RightSymm] : Feynman gauge projector for spin j, with momentum k, mass m, left side index prefix LeftPrefix, and right side index prefix RightPrefix. LeftSymm and RightSymm are True or False to specify whether to symmetrize the spinor indices.";
FGPropagator::usage="FGPropagator[S, k, m, LeftPrefix, RightPrefix, LeftSymm, RightSymm] : Feynman gauge propagator for spin j, with momentum k, mass m, left side index prefix LeftPrefix, and right side index prefix RightPrefix. LeftSymm and RightSymm are True or False to specify whether to symmetrize the spinor indices.";
FG\[CapitalTheta]::usage="FG\[CapitalTheta][Momenta, Mass, leftindiceslist, rightindiceslist] : The spin-1 projector in Feynman gauge. The default values for the left and right lists of spinor indices are {\[Alpha], \[Alpha]} and {\[Beta], \[Beta]}.";
FindBasis::usage="FindBasis[OptionsPattern[]] : Finds the basis of an expression. The default options include {pattern -> SHAA[a___, b___] | SHBB[a___, b___] | SHAB[a___, b___, c___]}.";
FindContactTerm::usage="FindContactTerm[leg] : Finds the contact term for a massless leg given a gauge-transformed expression.";
GenerateNumerics::usage="GenerateNumerics[label, MomentumConservationRule] : Generates numerical kinematics against the chosen label (e.g., $3point) for the momentum conservation rule (e.g., k1 -> k2 + k3). Options: {$Energy -> 100, $COM -> False, $Seed -> Automatic, MassConstraints -> $Assumptions, Iterations -> 20}";
Helicity::usage="Helicity[leg] : Gives the helicity for the declared massless leg.";
HighEnergyLimit::usage="HighEnergyLimit[MassiveLegsList, MasslessLegsList] : Gives the high-energy limit over the list of massive legs with their corresponding list of massless legs at high energies.";
HigherSpinDiff::usage="HigherSpinDiff[leg, Spin, SpinIndexB, SpinIndexA] : Takes the derivative with respect to the massive leg of spin Spin and the box & angle spinor index prefixes SpinIndexB and SpinIndexA.";
HigherSpinDiffA::usage="HigherSpinDiffA[leg, Spin, SpinIndexA] : Takes the derivative with respect to the massive leg of spin Spin and the angle spinor index prefix SpinIndexA.";
HigherSpinDiffB::usage="HigherSpinDiffB[leg, Spin, SpinIndexB] : Takes the derivative with respect to the massive leg of spin Spin and the box spinor index prefix SpinIndexB.";
HsPol::usage="HSPol[j,leg, \[Alpha], \[Beta], LGIndex1, LGIndex2] : Gives the higher-spin polarization for spin j for the massive leg with spinor index prefixes \[Alpha], \[Beta] and little group indices LGIndex1 and LGIndex2.";
IfN::usage="Gives True if the overall sign is -1.";
IfP::usage="Gives True if the overall sign is +1.";
ImposeReality::usage="ImposeReality[List] : Imposes reality over a list of declared legs. Sets TildeLeg[p] = p.";
k::usage="Prefix for the momenta.";
Leg::usage="Leg[Momenta] : Gives the leg index for the Momenta.";
LorToMandelstam::usage="Writes the contracted momenta (ki . kj) in terms of the Mandelstam variable SubscriptBox[s, ij].";
m::usage="m[i] : Mass of the leg i. Shortcut: ms";
MandelstamRules::usage="Gives the list of all Mandelstam variables in terms of AllIndependentMandelstams[].";
MandelstamtoLor::usage="Writes the Mandelstam variable SubscriptBox[s, ij] in terms of the contracted Lorentz momenta (ki . kj).";
MandelstamtoSH::usage="Writes the Mandelstam variable SubscriptBox[s, ij] in terms of the SH expression SHAB[i, j, i].";
ManifestGI::usage="ManifestGI[ReferenceSpinor -> {MasslessLeg1, MasslessLeg2}] : If the expression is independent of ReferenceSpinor, this command writes it in a manifestly gauge-invariant form by performing a basis transformation from ReferenceSpinor to a linear combination of two massless legs.";
MassConditions::usage="Extracts all terms from an expression that involve at least one mass factor.";
MassiveData::usage="Gives the association of the declared massive legs with their kinematic variables.";
MassiveMomenta::usage="MassiveMomenta[leg] : Gives the massive momentum for the massive leg.";
MassivePolarization::usage="MassivePolarization[leg] : Gives the massive polarization for the massive leg.";
MassiveQ::usage="Checks whether the variable is massive.";
MasslessData::usage="Gives the association of the declared massless legs with their kinematic variables.";
MasslessFieldStrength::usage="MasslessFieldStrength[leg] : Gives the massless field strength for the massless leg.";
MasslessLegs::usage="MasslessLegs[Momenta] : Gives the massless legs for the massless momenta.";
MasslessMomenta::usage="MasslessMomenta[leg] : Gives the massless momentum for the massless leg.";
MasslessPolarization::usage="MasslessPolarization[leg] : Gives the massless polarization for the massless leg.";
MasslessQ::usage="Checks whether the variable is massless.";
MassNumerics::usage="MassNumerics[label] : Gives the randomly generated mass values created against the label using GenerateNumerics.";
Met::usage="Met[\[Alpha], \[Beta]] : Gives the symmetric bilinear (indices with opposite signs) or antisymmetric bilinear (indices with the same sign) for SU(2)_L.";
Metd::usage="Metd[\[Alpha], \[Beta]] : Gives the symmetric bilinear (indices with opposite signs) or antisymmetric bilinear (indices with the same sign) for SU(2)_R.";
Metlg::usage="Metlg[J, K] : Gives the symmetric bilinear (indices with opposite signs) or antisymmetric bilinear (indices with the same sign) for SU(2)_LG.";
MI::usage="MI[a, i] : Joins the variables a and i to form a new variable.";
MIL::usage="MIL[list] : Joins the variables in the list. MIL[prefix, n] : Makes a list of indices with a prefix up to range n, i.e., gives {prefix1, prefix2, ..., prefixn}. The prefix can also be a negative variable.";
MlPol::usage="MlPol[i_, \[Alpha]_, \[Beta]_, h_, r_] : Gives the massless polarization for leg i, helicity h, reference spinor r, and undotted & dotted indices \[Alpha], \[Beta]. MlPol[i_, \[Alpha]_, \[Beta]_] : Gives the massless polarization for leg i, and undotted & dotted indices \[Alpha], \[Beta] if leg i is declared as massless. It uses the default values of helicity and reference spinor.";
MlQ::usage="Same as MasslessQ.";
Modp::usage="Modp[i] : Gives the magnitude of the spatial momentum vector |p_i|. Shortcut: mp";
Mom::usage="Mom[leg, \[Alpha], \[Beta]] : Gives the momentum for the leg with dotted and undotted indices \[Beta] and \[Alpha].";
momconsRule::usage="Momentum conservation rule defined using DeclareMomentumConservation.";
Momenta::usage="Momenta[leg] : Gives the momenta of the declared leg.";
MomentaNumerics::usage="MomentaNumerics[label] : Gives the list of numerical values for the momenta generated using GenerateNumerics against the label.";
MsIndex::usage="MsIndex[J, i] : Gives the red-colored massive little group index Ji.";
MsI::usage="Short form for MsIndex.";
MsPol::usage="MsPol[i_, \[Alpha]_, \[Beta]_, LGIndex1_:J1, LGIndex2_:J2] : Gives the massive spin-1 polarization for leg i with little group indices defaulting to J1 and J2.";
MsPolNonSymm::usage="MsPolNonSymm[i_, \[Alpha]_, \[Beta]_, LGIndex1_:J1, LGIndex2_:J2] : Gives the massive spin-1 polarization for leg i such that the little group indices are not symmetrized.";
NoLGScalar::usage="Breaks SHAB and SHBA into SHAA and SHBB.";
NoLGScalarWB::usage="Breaks SHAB and SHBA into SHAA and SHBB with all massive little group indices lowered and contracted with invariant bilinears. WB denotes With Bilinear.";
NoMassiveLGScalar::usage="Breaks SHAB and SHBA into SHAA and SHBB only if the middle leg is massive.";
NoMassiveLGScalarWB::usage="Breaks SHAB and SHBA into SHAA and SHBB only if the middle leg is massive, such that all massive little group indices are lowered and contracted with invariant bilinears. WB denotes With Bilinear.";
NoMasslessLGScalar::usage="Breaks SHAB and SHBA into SHAA and SHBB only if the middle leg is massless.";
NoMasslessLGScalarWB::usage="Same as NoMasslessLGScalar.";
NORM::usage="Choice of normalization for the massive polarization MsPol.";
NormQ::usage="To be set as True or False in Options for MsPol.";
NoScalar::usage="Breaks any scalar into angle and box spinors.";
NoSL2CScalar::usage="Breaks SHAA and SHBB into individual spinors.";
NoSL2CScalarWB::usage="Breaks SHAA and SHBB into individual spinors with spinor indices in the superscript contracted with Levi-Civita.";
NoSU2LScalar::usage="Breaks only the box scalars into individual spinors.";
NoSU2LScalarWB::usage="Breaks the box scalars into individual spinors with spinor indices in the superscript contracted with Levi-Civita.";
NoSU2RScalar::usage="Breaks only the angle scalars into individual spinors.";
NoSU2RScalarWB::usage="Breaks the angle scalars into individual spinors with spinor indices in the superscript contracted with Levi-Civita.";
NumericLabels::usage="List of labels for which numerics have been generated using the GenerateNumerics command.";
OpMlHW::usage="OpMlHW[leg] : Helicity Weight operator for the massless leg.";
OpMsHW::usage="OpMsHW[leg, I, J] : Helicity Weight operator for the massive leg where the massive little group indices {I, J} belong to {1, 2}.";
OpMsJ::usage="OpMsJ[leg, I, J] : Traceless massive little group generator for a leg where the massive little group indices {I, J} belong to {1, 2}.";
OPS::usage="OrderlessPatternSequence";
p::usage="p[leg][\[Mu]] : Gives the \[Mu]-th component of the lower p_\[Mu] for any leg. Shortcut: p";
Parity::usage="Applies a parity transformation over the SH expression. Shortcut: pt";
pMatLower::usage="pMatLower[leg] : Lower component matrix for the leg.";
pMatUpper::usage="pMatUpper[leg] : Upper component matrix for the leg.";
PowerContract::usage="Contracts powers with appropriate phase factors. This is the opposite of what PowerExpand does.";
Projector::usage="Projector[j, Momenta, Mass, \[Xi], Leftindicesprefixes:{\[Alpha], \[Alpha]}, Rightindicesprefixes:{\[Beta], \[Beta]}, LeftindicesSymmetrization_:False, RightindicesSymmetrization_:False] is the spin j projector in R_\[Xi] gauge. The last two arguments are reserved for symmetrizing the spinor indices. The respective indices are symmetrized if chosen as True.";
Propagator::usage="Propagator[j, Momenta, Mass, \[Xi], Leftindicesprefixes:{\[Alpha], \[Alpha]}, Rightindicesprefixes:{\[Beta], \[Beta]}, LeftindicesSymmetrization_:False, RightindicesSymmetrization_:False] is the spin j propagator in R_\[Xi] gauge. The last two arguments are reserved for symmetrizing the spinor indices. The respective indices are symmetrized if chosen as True.";
PropCoeff::usage="PropCoeff[j, r, d] := (-1/2)^r * (j! * (2j+d-2r-5)!!) / (r! * (j-2r)! * (2j+d-5)!!) is the binomial factor appearing in the r-th term of a spin j propagator in spacetime dimension d.";
PureGaugeTransformation::usage="PureGaugeTransformation[leg] : Applies the gauge transformation for the massless leg.";
PutCanonicalIndices::usage="Places canonical contracted indices across terms.";
PutCanonicalOrder::usage="Places canonical ordering in SH scalars.";
PutLGScalar::usage="Replaces SHAA and SHBB with SHAB.";
PutLGScalarFor::usage="PutLGScalarFor[leg1, leg2, leg3] : Replaces SHAA and SHBB with SHAB for the chosen legs. Arguments can also take patterns.";
PutMassiveLGScalar::usage="Replaces SHAA and SHBB with SHAB if the massive little group indices are contracted.";
PutMassiveLGScalarFor::usage="PutMassiveLGScalarFor[leg1, leg2, leg3] : Replaces SHAA and SHBB with SHAB if the massive little group indices are contracted for the chosen legs. Arguments can also take patterns.";
PutMasslessCondition::usage="PutMasslessCondition[leg_List] : Sets m[leg] == 0 for all legs in the expression. The default value for legs is the list AllMasslessLegs[].";
PutMasslessLGScalar::usage="Replaces SHAA and SHBB with SHAB by contracting massless legs.";
PutMasslessLGScalarFor::usage="PutMasslessLGScalarFor[leg1, leg2, leg3] : Replaces SHAA and SHBB with SHAB by contracting a massless leg for the chosen legs. Arguments can also take patterns.";
PutNumerics::usage="PutNumerics[label] : Converts an SH expression into numerics using numerical kinematics generated for the label via GenerateNumerics.";
PutOnShell::usage="Applies the on-shell inner product rules for massive spinors.";
PutOnShellComponent::usage="Applies the on-shell relations between momentum components.";
PutScalar::usage="Contracts the SL(2,C) as well as little group indices and constructs the angle and box scalars.";
PutSL2CScalar::usage="Contracts the SL(2,C) indices and constructs the angle and box scalars.";
PutSU2LScalar::usage="Contracts the SU(2)_L indices and constructs the box scalars.";
PutSU2RScalar::usage="Contracts the SU(2)_R indices and constructs the angle scalars.";
pVecLower::usage="pVecLower[leg] : Gives the momentum vector components p_\[Mu] for any leg.";
pVecUpper::usage="pVecUpper[leg] : Gives the momentum vector components p^\[Mu] for any leg.";
r::usage="Prefix for the reference spinor.";
RAMBO::usage="RAMBO[n, Energy, MassesList, Iterations] : Randomly generates numerical values of momenta such that they satisfy mass-shell conditions, their spatial momenta sum to zero, and their total energy equals Energy. Iterations specifies the number of steps used in the Newton-Raphson method, defaulting to 20.";
RAQ::usage="Refine AtomQ.";
ReferenceSpinor::usage="ReferenceSpinor[leg] : Gives the reference spinor for the massless leg.";
RefineAtomQ::usage="Refine AtomQ.";
RemoveReality::usage="RemoveReality[legs_List] : Removes the reality condition TildeLeg[leg] == leg from the specified legs list.";
RepeatedRule::usage="RepeatedRule[list] : Repeatedly applies the list of rules in succession until a fixed point is reached.";
ReplaceMomenta::usage="ReplaceMomenta[ListOfRules] : Replaces the momenta in the list of rules where each rule is of the form k1 -> k2 + k3.";
ReplaceSpinors::usage="ReplaceSpinors[ListOfRules] : Replaces spinors in the list of rules where each rule is a delayed rule of a spinor in terms of other spinors.";
ScaleMomenta::usage="ScaleMomenta[Rules] : Scales the momenta in the list of rules where each rule is of the form k1 -> \[Alpha] * k1. This command also scales the angle and box spinors by appropriate factors.";
ScaleSpinors::usage="ScaleSpinors[ListOfRules] : Scales the spinors. Every rule in the list of rules is of the form SHA[a, \[Alpha]_] :> \[Kappa] * SHA[a, \[Alpha]].";
Seed::usage="Option for GenerateNumerics.";
SetCanonicalIndices::usage="Applies PutCanonicalIndices automatically after every evaluation.";
SetComponentFormAssumption::usage="Adds \[CapitalEpsilon][i] \[Element] PositiveReals, Modp[i] \[Element] PositiveReals, p[i][0] \[Element] Reals, p[i][1] \[Element] Reals, p[i][2] \[Element] Reals, p[i][3] \[Element] Reals, \[Theta][i] \[Element] Reals, and \[Phi][i] \[Element] Reals to $Assumptions for all declared legs i.";
SetCounterZero::usage="Resets the counter to zero after every evaluation.";
SetDefaultOrdering::usage="SetDefaultOrdering[] : Resets the canonical ordering of SH scalars to default.";
SetSameMsIndices::usage="Sets massive little group indices to be identical.";
SHA::usage="SHA[leg, \[Alpha]] : Angle spinor for any leg and spinor index \[Alpha]. Shortcut: < or >";
SHAA::usage="SHAA[leg1, leg2] : Angle-Angle scalar for leg1 and leg2. Shortcut: <>";
SHAB::usage="SHAB[leg1, leg2, leg3] : Angle-Box scalar for leg1, leg2, and leg3. Shortcut: <]";
SHB::usage="SHB[leg, \[Alpha]] : Box spinor for any leg and spinor index \[Alpha]. Shortcut: [ or ]";
SHBA::usage="SHBA[leg1, leg2, leg3] : Box-Angle scalar for leg1, leg2, and leg3. Shortcut: [>";
SHBB::usage="SHBB[leg1, leg2] : Box-Box scalar for leg1 and leg2. Shortcut: []";
ShiftMomenta::usage="ShiftMomenta[RulesList] : Shifts the momenta up to a linear combination of other momenta. Each rule in the list is of the form k1 -> k1 + a * k2.";
SHToMandelstam::usage="Converts the spinor helicity scalars to Mandelstam variables.";
SimplifyComponentForm::usage="Simplifies the component form using RepeatedRule.";
SimplifyPolynomial::usage="Applies the PutOnShell, PutScalar, and ContractMetric rules using RepeatedRule.";
SimplifySchouten::usage="Simplifies an expression by applying the Schouten identities recursively.";
SignOf::usage="Gives the overall sign of the expression.";
sm::usage="sm[i, j] : Mandelstam variables (ki . kj). Shortcut: sm";
SM::usage="SM[i, j, ...] : Mandelstam variables (ki + kj + ...)^2.";
SphericalCoordinates::usage="Converts the Cartesian momentum components to spherical components.";
SplitMassive::usage="Same as NoMassiveLGScalar.";
SplitMassiveWB::usage="Same as NoMassiveLGScalarWB.";
SplitMassless::usage="Same as NoMasslessLGScalar.";
SplitMasslessWB::usage="Same as NoMasslessLGScalar.";
